social_posts.post_text:
On a 4th grade class trip from PS 20 Queens I went to the Museum of the City of New York. That future Urban Studies nerd is over the moon to be part of their Cocktails & Culture: Winter Soulstice Celebration, Thursday Dec 8. You can also check out the amazing City of Faith: Religion, Activism, and Urban Space curated by the brilliant @jeana31 which serves as a visual record of the nyc desi community with amazing artists like  @pardonmyhindi , @chitraganeshbkny , @jaishri.abichandani , and organizations @chhayacdc @drumnyc and many more. 

Plus enjoy Gingerbread Moscow mules from the @museumofcityny, delicious food from the @kwikmealnyc pop-up cafe. Explore other exhibits at the space including Food in New York: Bigger Than the Plate, where you can brush up your cookie-decorating skills at a hands-on gingerbread cookie decorating session with master baker and cake decorator Amy Scherber of @amysbread.  FREE with museum admission.

DJ Rekha (born Rekha Malhotra) is a DJ, producer, curator, and educator. They have forever changed South Asian Diasporic dance music. 

DJ Rekha is the founder for Basement Bhangra and they have shared the stage with many artists including AR Rahman, Yoko Ono, the Roots, M.I.A and have performed in festivals, clubs, and community spaces worldwide including the inaugural Women’s March and Obama’s White House, London Mela, 5X Fest, SXSW, Sundance.

Queens gets the music. When I was asked by SummerStage to produce an event for Queens Live at Flushing Meadow Corona Park, I was beyond excited. This is the place I and so many folx have come for years to take a break and gather with friends, fam, and community. The inspiration for making the Basement Bhangra Bacchanal is the rich musical upbringing this borough has given me, the cultural vibrancy of the West Indian and Punjabi communities of the southern part of the borough, and the rich talent of the diaspora from areas that defy borders. 

Catch me and some of the hottest South Asian artists in the game at SummerStage in Flushing Meadows Corona Park, Queens on July 23rd, 2023. We'll be bringing you a FREE show packed with music, energy, and community vibes. Huge shoutout to @summerstage, @CPFNY, and @_productofculture_ for making this happen. Don't miss out on the show of the year with @malkitsingh_goldenstar, @djanamusic, @rolexrasathy, @paramsinghmusic, @dholianuradha, and @theshadownotes #Queens #FlushingMeadows #SummerStage #nycdanceparty #freeconcert #bhangra #bacchanal #chutneymusic #socamusic #bhangradance #ProductOfCulture

Get ready for Basement Bhangra Bacchanal in Queens! 🎵✨

Mark your calendars for July 23rd and dive into the sounds of the first ever Basement Bhangra in Queens. We’re bringing the heat to Flushing Meadows Corona Park with an epic lineup — the legendary Malkit Singh with a live band, the all-star Chutney Soca mainstay DJ Ana, the jazz and R&B-influenced Carnatic visionary Rolex Rasathy, the chart-topping sensation Param Singh, the self-taught dhol master Dholi Anuradha, and the Shadow Notes, drawing mystical hooks and beats from Trinidad and Punjab.

There would be no Basement Bhangra without Queens, and this Bacchanal edition is all about embracing the vibrant culture of West Indian and Punjabi communities of the southern part of the borough while celebrating the border-defying talent of the diaspora.

Grab your crew and get ready to dance. Join us on July 23rd at Flushing Meadows Corona Park and let’s make memories that’ll last a lifetime. 🙌🌟 

Huge shoutout to @summerstage, @CPFNY, and @_productofculture_ for making this happen. Don’t miss out on the show of the year with @djrekha, @malkitsingh_goldenstar, @djanamusic, @rolexrasathy, @paramsinghmusic, @dholianuradha, and #theshadownotes #Queens #FlushingMeadows #SummerStage #nycdanceparty #freeconcert #bhangra #bacchanal #chutneymusic #socamusic #bhangradance

Pride may be over, but the party continues, this time at the historic @icepalacefi on Fire Island’s Cherry Grove. DRAGISTAN brings to you NYC’s premiere queer desi DJs and drag artists, hosted by your favorite aunty @lawhorevagistan in collaboration with @fireislandresidency. This is a first of its kind event on Fire Island, celebrating queer South Asian music, dance, drag, and community. Make a day of it, come in the afternoon and explore the bars, beaches, and longstanding queer community of Fire Island before the party. Performances at 9pm! 

Tickets go on sale Wednesday July 5: www.redeyetickets.com. Ticket options include general admission, return ferry to Sayville, and return buses from Sayville to downtown Brooklyn and Manhattan.

With over 30 years in the industry, Malkit has hit 36 countries, dropped 21 albums, and racked up countless awards along the way. 🌍🎶 Brace yourself for a legendary performance, featuring his iconic anthem Gur Nalon Ishq Mitha, a Basement Bhangra mainstay! 🎵✨ Don't miss out on his explosive hit Kali Ainak, currently rocking the charts 📈🔥 #BhangraKing #PunjabiIcon

🌟 Join us in welcoming the dynamic DJ Ana (@djana_music) to our incredible lineup. 🎧🎉 Born in Canada and raised in Trinidad, DJ Ana has been captivating audiences since the age of 8. With her impressive background as a Chutney Soca DJ and a radio announcer/DJ on LIT 102.3 FM, she brings an irresistible energy to every performance. 🎶💥

Don't miss DJ Ana's electrifying sets, featuring a fusion of Soca, Dancehall, Reggae, Hip Hop, EDM, Top 40, Pop, Latin, and more! 🎵✨ She was the first Trinidadian DJ ever featured in The Fader, and her talent has taken her on tours worldwide, alongside international cricketer DJ Bravo. Get ready to experience DJ Ana's infectious beats and vibrant presence at our upcoming event. 🔥🌍

🌟 Give a warm welcome to the incredible @rolexrasathy, as she joins our epic line up! 🎤🎉 Based in New York with her roots deep in Queens, she's a singer-songwriter and creative visionary with a unique blend of Carnatic music, jazz, R&B, and hip-hop influences. Brace yourself for the magic of her experimental English/Tamil EP "Vellavattai," a soul-stirring creation born from a life-changing experience in Sri Lanka. Since then, she's collaborated with industry stars and rocked stages around the world. 🌍🎵 Her single "Raavanan" was a global hit and selected by BBC Asian Network as 'Track of the Week'. She soon after collaborated on the song “Nalla Pilla” which has also been celebrated globally as a brown girl empowerment anthem 🌟💪 Don’t miss out on a chance to be mesmerised by this one-of-a-kind talent 🎶❤️ #RolexRasathy #CreativeVisionary

Basement Bhangra BACCHANAL brings together the rich musical upbringing Queens has given me. Curating is one of my biggest joys, finding the hottest artists from all over the diaspora to represent a dynamic and eclectic sonic range of culture. This show comes about after decades of the partnership between Basement Bhangra and City Parks SummerStage, and there's no more fitting accessible space for all of us than Flushing Meadows Corona Park. It's an honor to spin at the at the park where this young immigrant kid was looking for a place for themselves.
